## TSPS - Evaluation and Performance Measurement Services

### Tender Information

* **Reference Number**: PW-22-01005735
* **Solicitation Number**: FEDDEV-2022-0802/001
* **Publication Date**: August 30, 2022
* **Tender Closing Date**: September 14, 2022, at 2:00 PM
* **Expected Contract Start Date**: Not specified
* **Expected Contract End Date**: Not specified

### Description of the Requirement

FedDev Ontario is seeking a qualified contractor to provide evaluation and performance measurement services under the Task and Solutions Professional Services (TSPS) method of supply. The services will focus on supporting the agency's evaluation and performance measurement activities, as well as providing transfer of knowledge and job shadowing for training purposes.

The contractor and their proposed resources must work with FedDev Ontario to carry out evaluation and performance measurement work, transfer knowledge, and job shadow for training purposes. In addition to delivering the projects outlined in the evaluation plan, the contractor may be required to assist with the development and validation of evaluation or performance measurement methodologies to meet the requirements of the 2016 Treasury Board Policy on Results.

### Security Requirements

The security level required for this contract is Secret, with a minimum security level for company and resources required.

### Trade Agreements

The following trade agreements apply to this contract:

* World Trade Organization Agreement on Government Procurement (WTO-AGP)
* Canada-Chile Free Trade Agreement (CCFTA)
* Canada-Peru Free Trade Agreement (CPFTA)
* Canada-Colombia Free Trade Agreement
* Canada-Panama Free Trade Agreement
* Canada-Honduras Free Trade Agreement
* Canada-Korea Free Trade Agreement (CKFTA)
* Canadian Free Trade Agreement (CFTA)

### Contact Information

For any questions or concerns, please contact Dianna Pietsch, Contracting Authority, at (519) 500-5937 or dianna.pietsch@feddevontario.gc.ca. 139 Northfield Drive West, Suite 101, Waterloo, ON N2L 5A6.

### Additional Information

The Task and Solutions Professional Services (TSPS) method of supply is subject to quarterly refresh cycles. If you wish to become a "Qualified SA Holder," please contact SPTS.TSPS@TPSGC-PWGSC.GC.CA.  [Note: This contact information should be provided in all government tender announcements.](https
